To calculate the average dependency distance, we first need to analyze the sentence and identify the head word for each word. Here is the analysis:

1. Första - modifier of 'delen', dependency distance: 1
   Första -> delen

2. delen - head of 'Första', dependent of 'består', dependency distance: 1
   delen -> består

3. består - head of 'delen', dependent of 'av', dependency distance: 1
   består -> av

4. av - head of 'består', dependent of no head (top), dependency distance: N/A
   However, as 'av' is the head, consider dependency with modifier 'studie' instead, dependency distance: 2 (including the word 'en')
   studie -> av

5. en - modifier of 'studie', dependency distance: 1
   en -> studie

6. studie - head of 'en' and dependent of 'av', dependency distance: 1
   However, as 'studie' is the head of 'en' and is in turn dependent on 'av', use its dependency distance with 'av' above
   studie -> av

7. av - head of 'studie', dependent of 'litteratur', dependency distance: 2 (including the word 'med')
   litteratur -> av

8. litteratur - head of no dependent word here (its 'dependent word' is av - inverse), but syntactically dependent of 'syfte', dependency distance: 4 (including the word 'med')
   litteratur -> syfte

9. med - modifier of 'litteratur', dependency distance: 1
   med -> litteratur

10. syfte - head of 'litteratur', dependent of 'att', dependency distance: 1
    syfte -> att

11. att - head of 'syfte', head of the embedded sentence, 'dependent of no head (clause)'), dependency distance: N/A
    However, for the purposes of calculating the average distance, we will assign att as dependent of main sentence predicate 'består', distance: 5 (including the word 'syfte')
    syfte -> består 

12. få - head of the embedded clause, no head dependency, dependency distance: N/A
    However, consider dependency with the head 'att', dependency distance: 1
    få -> att

13. en - modifier of 'bild', dependency distance: 1
    en -> bild

14. övergripande - modifier of 'bild', dependency distance: 1
    övergripande -> bild

15. bild - head of 'en' and 'övergripande', and dependent of 'få', dependency distance: 1
    bild -> få

16. av - head of 'den forskning', dependent of 'få', dependency distance: 2 (including word 'en', 'övergripande', 'bild' will get 'att' through transitivity, distance of get: 4 above)) 
    However, calculate dependency distance from a modifier instead (den forskning above), from head: 3 (den forskning will get 'att' through transitivity and on, distance of get 'att' at 4) below), head is therefore better taken as 'att' while directly having a following head of 'den forskning'.
    The appropriate sequence from direct is therefore: få -> (sent- main), av -> den forskning
    Not attached ('att'), head attached, to calculate later in 'att'

17. den - modifier of 'forskning', dependency distance: 1
    den -> forskning

18. forskning - head of 'den' and 'som', dependent of 'av', dependency distance: 1

19. som - head of 'berör', dependent of 'forskning', dependency distance: 1
    However, head can be assigned from head of forskning direct which is to calculate from the 'av' which is at a higher dependency head location - so higher sequence head, location being - (used av so move down below), then head for berör while has dependency - has to be higher to lower which goes location wise) 
   - berör therefore head given better higher head transitivity
   better therefore for lower use location reference - then next upper then reference main 'att' - which make easier head following higher level give correct level at 3 steps after in distance: below head) att) -> berör.

20. lärande - head of no word above but get dependency - depends on 'på', modified by no words under head berör, (which has more than 7 total main), dependency distance: 1

21. på - head of 'lärande', dependent of 'berör', dependency distance: 1
   